On April 6, 2020, several nominations were sent to the Senate for various positions. These nominations include Jason Abend from Virginia, who was nominated to be the Inspector General of the Department of Defense, replacing Jon T. Rymer who resigned. Katherine A. Crytzer from Tennessee was nominated to be the Inspector General of the Tennessee Valley Authority, replacing Richard W. Moore who resigned. Andrew A. De Mello from Massachusetts was nominated to be the Inspector General of the Department of Education, replacing Kathleen S. Tighe who resigned. Brian D. Miller from Virginia was nominated to be the Special Inspector General for Pandemic Recovery, a new position. Lastly, Peter Michael Thomson from Louisiana was nominated to be the Inspector General of the Central Intelligence Agency, replacing David B. Buckley who resigned.